# TypeScript Configuration Package Rules

## Purpose
This package provides shared TypeScript configurations for all projects in the monorepo.

## Available Configurations
- `base.json` - Base TypeScript configuration
- `nestjs.json` - Configuration for NestJS applications
- `nextjs.json` - Configuration for Next.js applications
- `react-library.json` - Configuration for React library packages

## Base Configuration Pattern
```json
{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/tsconfig",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "ES2020",
    "lib": ["ES2020"],
    "module": "NodeNext",
    "moduleResolution": "NodeNext",
    "strict": true,
    "esModuleInterop": true,
    "skipLibCheck": true,
    "forceConsistentCasingInFileNames": true,
    "declaration": true,
    "declarationMap": true,
    "sourceMap": true
  }
}
```

## Usage in Apps/Packages
```json
{
  "extends": "@repo/typescript-config/nextjs.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"],
      "@lib/*": ["./src/lib/*"]
    }
  },
  "include": ["src/**/*", "next-env.d.ts"],
  "exclude": ["node_modules", ".next"]
}
```

## NestJS Configuration
```json
{
  "extends": "./base.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "module": "CommonJS",
    "moduleResolution": "Node",
    "emitDecoratorMetadata": true,
    "experimentalDecorators": true,
    "target": "ES2021",
    "outDir": "./dist",
    "rootDir": "./src",
    "incremental": true
  }
}
```

## Next.js Configuration
```json
{
  "extends": "./base.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "lib": ["DOM", "DOM.Iterable", "ES2020"],
    "module": "ESNext",
    "moduleResolution": "Bundler",
    "jsx": "preserve",
    "plugins": [{ "name": "next" }],
    "noEmit": true
  }
}
```

## React Library Configuration
```json
{
  "extends": "./base.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "lib": ["ES2020", "DOM", "DOM.Iterable"],
    "module": "ESNext",
    "moduleResolution": "Bundler",
    "jsx": "react-jsx",
    "declaration": true,
    "declarationMap": true
  }
}
```

## Key Compiler Options

### Strict Mode (always enable)
- `strict: true` - Enable all strict checks
- `noImplicitAny: true` - Error on implicit any
- `strictNullChecks: true` - Strict null checks

### Module Resolution
- NestJS: `"module": "CommonJS"`, `"moduleResolution": "Node"`
- Next.js: `"module": "ESNext"`, `"moduleResolution": "Bundler"`
- Libraries: `"module": "ESNext"`, `"moduleResolution": "Bundler"`

### Decorators (NestJS)
- `"emitDecoratorMetadata": true`
- `"experimentalDecorators": true`

### Path Aliases
Define in consuming project's tsconfig:
```json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "baseUrl": ".",
    "paths": {
      "@/*": ["./src/*"],
      "@repo/api": ["../../packages/api/src"],
      "@repo/ui/*": ["../../packages/ui/src/*"]
    }
  }
}
```

## Monorepo Considerations
- Use `references` for project references
- Enable `composite: true` for referenced projects
- Use `declarationMap: true` for go-to-definition

```json
{
  "references": [
    { "path": "../../packages/api" },
    { "path": "../../packages/ui" }
  ]
}
```

## Best Practices
- Keep base config strict and minimal
- Let specialized configs extend base
- Don't disable strict checks without good reason
- Use `skipLibCheck: true` for faster builds
- Include `$schema` for IDE support
- Document any non-obvious settings with comments
